<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="py-20" style="background:#FFFFFF">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <p class="sl gt mb-3">Common Questions</p>
      <h2 style="font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);line-height:.95;color:#1A1A1A;letter-spacing:-.01em">RESIDENTIAL ROOFING FAQ</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
        How much does a residential roof replacement cost in Tampa Bay?
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">A typical residential roof replacement in Tampa Bay ranges from $8,000 to $25,000+ depending on roof size, pitch complexity, material choice (asphalt shingles, metal, or tile), and whether structural repairs are needed. Factors like second-story access, chimney and skylight flashing, and code-required upgrades can also affect pricing. Happy Roof provides free, detailed estimates with no hidden fees - call <a href="tel:8135957663" class="call-tracking-number" style="color:#3B9FD9;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600">(813) 595-7663</a> for a personalized quote.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
        What is the best roofing material for Florida homes?
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">The best material depends on your budget, aesthetic preference, and long-term goals. Architectural shingles (Owens Corning Duration HDZ or GAF Timberline HDZ) offer the best value with 130+ MPH wind ratings and 25–30 year lifespans. Standing seam metal lasts 40–60 years and reflects solar heat, reducing energy bills by up to 25%. Concrete and clay tile deliver a classic Florida look with 50+ year lifespans. Happy Roof installs all three and can help you choose the right fit for your home.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
